        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\t\t\t \n\n                 \t\n\n\n\t « All Events\n\n\t\n\tThis event has passed.\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\tParallel Art Show (PAS)\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tSeptember 27, 2025 @ 10:00 am - October 18, 2025 @ 4:00 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\nThe Salt Spring National Art Prize (SSNAP) is a biennial, juried competition and exhibition of Canadian contemporary art. Held on Salt Spring Island, BC, SSNAP celebrates and promotes artists from across the country through a major exhibition, significant awards, and national recognition.\nThe Parallel Art Show (PAS) is a juried exhibition showcasing artists from the Southern Gulf Islands, presented alongside the Salt Spring National Art Prize. Featuring a diverse range of local talent, PAS highlights innovative contemporary work across disciplines and runs concurrently with SSNAP at ArtSpring. \nOpening Gala for PAS – 6-8pm Sept 28 (*No Tickets)\nPas Exhibition in ArtSpring Gallery – Sept 27 – Oct 19, 2025\nClosing gala awards night for SSNAP + PAS – 6-9pm Oct 18 (*Tickets required. On Sale Now!)\nPAS Artists:\n\nMatt Adolf • David Allan • Seth Berkowitz • Chintan Bolliger\nCarole Bondaroff • Sally Born • Joan Carrigan • Leo Chan • Gary Cherneff\nStefanie Denz • Kyle Durant • Mimi Fujino • Dina González Mascaró\nDiana Hayes • Martin Herbert • Jen Holmes • Elisabeth Jahren\nDavid James • John David James • Cathryn Jenkins • Amy Jones\nGarry Kaye • Laura Keil • Kasumi Lampitoc • Bob Leatherbarrow\nCheryl Long • Jennifer Maksymetz • Gillian McConnell\nLarry Melious • Chris Metze • Robert Moss • Doreen Palme\nPatricia Parkes • Max Parsons • Elaine Potter • Matt Robertson\n\n\nLexane Rousseau • Andrea Russell • Anette Schrage • Katherine Scott\nKaren Selk • Sandy Shreve • Jeannette Sirois • Nathalie St-Amant\nAlicja Swiatlon • Anna Szul • Melanie Thompson • Ida Marie Threadkell\nSherry Williams • April Winter • Margo Zak\n\n \nPAS JURY\n Steven McNeil – Chief Curator & Director of Collections and Exhibitions, Art Gallery of Greater Victoria\nKim Pollard – Artist, curator, consultant, gallerist, and mentor based on Pender Island\nAlexandra Montgomery – Former Director/CEO of the Bill Reid Gallery and Gardiner Museum, now based on Salt Spring Island\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t Details \n\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tStart:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t September 27, 2025 @ 10:00 am \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tEnd:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t October 18, 2025 @ 4:00 pm \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\tEvent Category: Gallery Exhibits & Events\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tWebsite:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t saltspringartprize.ca \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\n\n\tOrganizer\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tSSNAP\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tPhone\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t250-931-1141\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tEmail\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tinfo@saltspringartprize.ca\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tView Organizer Website\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t Venue \n\t\n\t\t\t\t ArtSpring – Gallery \n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n100 Jackson Avenue\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tSalt Spring Island,\n\n\n\tV8K 2V8\n\n\tCanada\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t+ Google Map\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tPhone\n\t\t\t\t\t 250.537.2102 \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tAdd to calendar\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\tGoogle Calendar\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\tiCalendar\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\tOutlook 365\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\tOutlook Live\t\n\n\