    "https://schema.org/mainContentOfPage": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\t\t\t \n\n                 \t\n\n\n\t « All Events\n\n\t\n\tThis event has passed.\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\tPIANO HEIST\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\tApril 1, 2025 @ 7:30 pm - 9:30 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t-\n\t\t\t\t\t\t$5 – $35\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\nAPR 1 | 7:30pm | Lifelong friends, colleagues, and multi-talented musicians Nico Rhodes and Patrick Courtin were shocked and appalled by their realization that piano just isn’t cool anymore. This set off a quest to redeem the keyboard and reinstate its reputation as the greatest instrument of ALL TIME! \n\n\nArmed with the music of the greatest composers, songwriters, and performers of the past 300 years, and the technology of the 21st century – Nico and Patrick deliver everything from classical piano raptures and bombastic boogie woogie to romantic piano ballads and 80’s keyboard synth as they battle it out in their show Piano Heist! What ensues is a mishmash of theatrical wonder, comedy, audience participation, heartfelt stories, a pinch of history, and a world of musical madness.\n\n\nThank you to Kate Merry for sponsoring this performance.\nBUY TICKETS\nACT ONE\nBACH TO THE BEGINNING\n Minuet in G major – J.S. Bach\n Goldberg Variations No.1 – J.S. Bach\n Toccata and Fugue – J.S. Bach\n Phantom of the Opera – A.L. Webber\n Hit the Road Jack – Ray Charles\n In the Hall of the Mountain King – Edvard Grieg\n Imperial March – John Williams\n Habanera (Carmen) – Georges Bizet\n Jurassic Park – John Williams\n Sir Duke – Stevie Wonder\n Hockey Night in Canada – Dolores Claman\nDJ LUDWIG\n Sonata No.16 in C Major – Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart\n Für Elise – Ludwig van Beethoven\n Fantasie Impromptu – Frédéric Chopin\n Gymnopedies –Erik Satie\n Hungarian Dance n.6 – Johannes Brahms\n Rhapsody in Blue – Georges Gershwin\n Hungarian Rhapsody n.2 – Franz Liszt\nTWO NIGHTS WITH CHOPIN\n Nocturne No.2 in Eb – Frédéric Chopin\n Freddie’s Rag – Rhodes/Chopin\nAND ALL THAT JAZZ!\nSing, Sing, Sing – Benny Goodman\nMoondance – Van Morrison\nI don’t mean anything – Duke Ellington\n Blue Rondo a la Turk – Brubeck\nLand of the Misty Giants – Oscar Peterson\n A Date with An Improvisation – Nico Rhodes\nSO, YOU THINK YOU CAN DANCE?\n Tico Tico –   Zequinha de Abreu\nINTERMISSION\nACT TWO\nFRIGHT OF THE BUMBLE BEE\n If I Only Had a Brain – Arlen\n Bumble Bee Boogie – Korsakov/Rhodes\n Eye of the Tiger – Survivor\nCHEERS TO THE PIANO PEOPLE\n Great balls of fire – Otis Blackwell/Jack Hammer\n What’d I Say – Ray Charles\n Green onions – Booker T and the MG’S\n House of the Rising Sun – Georgia Turner/Bert Martin\n Light my fire – The Doors\n Hey Jude – The Beatles\n Tiny Dancer – Elton John\n Crocodile Rock- Elton John\n Superstition – Stevie Wonder\n Popcorn – Gershon Kingsley\n Money – Abba\n The final countdown – Europe\nTHE BETRAYAL\n Claire the Lonely – Claude Debussy\n Je vais Survivre – Freddie Perren & Dino Fekaris\nSALOON BATTLE aka HOEDOWN ALLA TURCA\n Rondo Alla Turca – Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart\nRHAPSODIC REUNION\n Bohemian Rhapsody – Queen\nREVENGE OF THE GUITAR\nGuitar battle – Nico Rhodes\nOde to Joy – Ludwig van Beethoven\nKEYS ARE THE CHAMPIONS\nWe are the Champions – Queen\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t Details \n\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tDate:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t April 1, 2025 \n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tTime:\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t7:30 pm - 9:30 pm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tCost:\n\t\t\t\t $5 – $35 \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\tEvent Category: ArtSpring Presents 2024-2025\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\n\n\tOrganizer\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tArtSpring\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t Venue \n\t\n\t\t\t\t ArtSpring – Theatre \n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n100 Jackson Avenue\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tSalt Spring Island,\n\n\tBC\n\n\tV8K 2V8\n\n\tCanada\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\