        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "&lt;p&gt;OPENING EVENT: Saturday April 5 | 5pm-7pm In Hamlet’s &quot;To Be or Not To Be&quot; soliloquy he contemplates life and death, using “Undiscovered Country&quot; as a metaphor for the unknown [&hellip;]&lt;/p&gt;\\n"
